## Connect Your Agent

### ElizaOS

In your ElizaOS character config:
```json
{
  "settings": {
    "chains": {
      "ethereum": {
        "rpcUrl": "http://localhost:8545",
        "chainId": 1
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### LangChain + Web3.py (Python)

```python
from web3 import Web3

w3 = Web3(Web3.HTTPProvider("http://localhost:8545"))
account = w3.eth.account.from_key("0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80")
print(f"Balance: {w3.from_wei(w3.eth.get_balance(account.address), 'ether')} ETH")
```

### ethers.js

```typescript
import { ethers } from "ethers";

const provider = new ethers.JsonRpcProvider("http://localhost:8545");
const wallet = new ethers.Wallet(
  "0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80",
  provider
);
```

### viem

```typescript
import { createWalletClient, http } from "viem";
import { mainnet } from "viem/chains";
import { privateKeyToAccount } from "viem/accounts";

const client = createWalletClient({
  account: privateKeyToAccount("0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80"),
  chain: { ...mainnet, rpcUrls: { default: { http: ["http://localhost:8545"] } } },
  transport: http("http://localhost:8545"),
});
```

### Any HTTP Agent (curl)

```bash
# Get latest block number
curl -s http://localhost:8545 \
  -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"eth_blockNumber","params":[],"id":1}'

# Get ETH balance
curl -s http://localhost:8545 \
  -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"eth_getBalance","params":["0xf39Fd6e51aad88F6F4ce6aB8827279cffFb92266","latest"],"id":1}'
```

## Stress-Test Scenarios

Use `dokrypt scenario` to simulate market conditions:

```bash
dokrypt scenario list                                # List all scenarios
dokrypt scenario run market-crash                    # 50% price crash
dokrypt scenario run market-crash --severity 80      # 80% price drop
dokrypt scenario run oracle-failure --hours 12       # Oracle stale 12h
dokrypt scenario run liquidity-drain --percent 90    # 90% liquidity removed
dokrypt scenario run gas-spike --gwei 500            # Gas price to 500 gwei
dokrypt scenario run whale-dump                      # Large holder sells
dokrypt scenario reset                               # Restore pre-scenario state
```

## Useful Commands

```bash
dokrypt status                    # Check running services
dokrypt chain info                # Chain details
dokrypt chain set-balance <addr> <eth>   # Fund any address
dokrypt chain time-travel 1h      # Advance time
dokrypt chain mine 10             # Mine blocks
dokrypt snapshot save clean       # Save state
dokrypt snapshot restore clean    # Restore state
dokrypt down                      # Stop everything
```
